# User Pages — API Call Optimization Plan

> **Goal**: Reduce HTTP round-trips, eliminate N+1 patterns, and move filtering server-side for all User-related pages — without affecting other pages.

---

## 1 — Current State: API Call Audit

### 1.1 UsersPage.jsx (List page)

| # | API Call | Trigger | Payload Size | Problem |
|---|---------|---------|--------------|---------|
| 1 | `GET /users?page=&limit=20&search=` | Page load, search, page change | 20 user rows | ✅ Paginated |
| 2 | `GET /clients?page=1&limit=1000` | Mount (once) | **ALL clients** | 🔴 Fetches 1000 clients just to build filter dropdown names |
| 3 | `GET /users?page=1&limit=1000` | Mount (once) | **ALL users** | 🔴 Fetches 1000 users just to extract unique filter options (client_type, seniority, location) |
| 4–43 | 2 × N calls inside [UsersTable.jsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/components/users/UsersTable.jsx) | After users render | N = 20 rows × 2 calls each | 🔴 **N+1 pattern**: per-user `GET /projects?limit=1&poc_user_id=X` + `GET /engagements?limit=1000&poc_user_id=X` |

**Total on first load: 3 + 2N (≈ 43 requests) with N = 20 user rows.**

> [!CAUTION]
> The N+1 in [UsersTable](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/components/users/UsersTable.jsx#17-179) is **twice as bad** as the Client page — it fires 2 HTTP calls per row (projects + engagements), totaling up to 40 parallel requests just for counts.

### 1.2 UserDetails.jsx (Single user view)

| # | API Call | Trigger | Problem |
|---|---------|---------|---------|
| 1 | `GET /users/<id>` | Page load | ✅ OK |
| 2 | `GET /projects?page=&limit=20&poc_user_id=<id>` | Page load | ✅ OK — paginated |
| 3 | `GET /engagements?limit=1000&poc_user_id=<id>` (via [EngagementAssignmentsTable](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/components/engagements/EngagementAssignmentsTable.jsx#5-102)) | Page load | ⚠️ Limit 1000 — OK for now |

**Total: 3 requests — acceptable, no changes needed.**

### 1.3 UserEditPage.jsx

| # | API Call | Trigger | Problem |
|---|---------|---------|---------|
| 1 | `GET /clients?page=1&limit=1000` | Mount | 🔴 Fetches 1000 clients for dropdown |
| 2 | `GET /lookups` | Mount | ✅ OK — returns hasamex_users |
| 3 | `GET /users/<id>` | Mount | ✅ OK |

**Total: 3 requests.** Call #1 is excessive.

---

## 2 — Root Cause Analysis

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["UsersPage mounts"] --> B["fetchUsers (paginated)"]
    A --> C["fetchClients (1000)"]
    A --> D["fetchUsers (1000)"]
    B --> E["UsersTable renders"]
    E --> F["2N × fetch per user row"]
    style F fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#333
    style C fill:#ffa94d,stroke:#333
    style D fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#333
```

| Issue | Severity | Root Cause |
|-------|----------|------------|
| **N+1 project+engagement counts** | 🔴 Critical | [UsersTable.jsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/components/users/UsersTable.jsx) fires `GET /projects?poc_user_id=X` + `GET /engagements?poc_user_id=X` per row |
| **1000-client fetch for filters** | 🔴 High | [UsersPage](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/pages/users/UsersPage.jsx#14-295) downloads entire clients table for filter dropdown names |
| **1000-user fetch for filter options** | 🔴 High | Downloads all users to extract unique seniorities, locations, client_types |
| **Client list on Edit page** | ⚠️ Medium | [UserEditPage](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/pages/users/UserEditPage.jsx#13-387) fetches 1000 clients for a dropdown |
| **No backend aggregation** | 🔴 Critical | `GET /users` returns flat rows; no project/engagement counts |

---

## 3 — Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Backend — `GET /users/summary`

#### [MODIFY] [users.py](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/backend/routes/users.py)

New endpoint returning paginated users with pre-computed counts:

```python
@users_bp.route('/summary', methods=['GET'])
def get_users_summary():
    """
    Returns paginated users with project_count and engagement_count
    pre-computed server-side. Replaces 3 + 2N frontend calls with 1.
    Also supports server-side filtering by client_id, client_type,
    seniority, and location.
    """
```

Uses batch `GROUP BY` queries (same pattern as `/clients/summary`):

```sql
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) FROM projects WHERE poc_user_id IN (...) GROUP BY poc_user_id;
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) FROM engagements WHERE poc_user_id IN (...) GROUP BY poc_user_id;
```

Each user row includes:
```json
{ "project_count": 3, "engagement_count": 7 }
```

Also supports server-side filtering with multi-value params:
- `client_id=1,2,3`
- `client_type=Hedge Fund,Consulting`
- `seniority=Senior,Mid`
- `location=London,New York`

---

### Phase 2: Backend — `GET /users/filter-options`

#### [MODIFY] [users.py](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/backend/routes/users.py)

Returns distinct filter values in **a single lightweight call** — replaces fetching 1000 clients + 1000 users:

```python
@users_bp.route('/filter-options', methods=['GET'])
def get_user_filter_options():
    """Returns distinct values for filter dropdowns."""
    # client_names: SELECT DISTINCT client_name FROM clients ORDER BY client_name
    # client_types: SELECT DISTINCT client_type FROM users WHERE client_type IS NOT NULL
    # seniorities: SELECT DISTINCT seniority FROM users WHERE seniority IS NOT NULL
    # locations: SELECT DISTINCT location FROM users WHERE location IS NOT NULL (via lk_location)
```

Response:
```json
{
  "client_names": ["Acme Corp", "Beta Inc"],
  "client_types": ["Hedge Fund", "Consulting"],
  "seniorities": ["Senior", "Mid-Level"],
  "locations": ["London, UK", "New York, US"]
}
```

---

### Phase 3: Backend — `GET /users/form-lookups`

#### [MODIFY] [users.py](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/backend/routes/users.py)

Single endpoint for Edit page dropdowns:

```python
@users_bp.route('/form-lookups', methods=['GET'])
def get_user_form_lookups():
    """Returns clients list + hasamex_users for Edit/Create forms."""
```

---

### Phase 4: Frontend — UsersPage.jsx

#### [MODIFY] [UsersPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/pages/users/UsersPage.jsx)

- Replace [fetchUsers](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/users.js#3-30) + [fetchClients(1000)](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/clients.js#3-20) + [fetchUsers(1000)](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/users.js#3-30) with:
  - `fetchUsersSummary()` — 1 call for paginated users with counts
  - `fetchUserFilterOptions()` — 1 call for filter dropdowns (once at mount)
- Move filter logic to **server-side** via query params
- Remove client-side `filter()` on already-paginated data (currently breaks pagination)

**Before (3 + 2N calls) → After (2 calls, then 1 per search/page change)**

---

### Phase 5: Frontend — UsersTable.jsx

#### [MODIFY] [UsersTable.jsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/components/users/UsersTable.jsx)

- **Remove** entire `useEffect` that fires 2N calls (lines 26-59)
- **Remove** `counts` state, `http` import
- Read `project_count` and `engagement_count` directly from user data (from summary endpoint)

**Before:** 40 additional HTTP requests per render.
**After:** 0 additional HTTP requests.

---

### Phase 6: Frontend — UserEditPage.jsx

#### [MODIFY] [UserEditPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/pages/users/UserEditPage.jsx)

- Replace [fetchClients(1000)](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/clients.js#3-20) + [fetchLookups()](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/lookups.js#3-7) with single `fetchUserFormLookups()`
- Parallel call alongside [fetchUserById(id)](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/users.js#31-35)

**Before (3 calls) → After (2 calls)**

---

### Phase 7: Frontend API Layer

#### [MODIFY] [users.js](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/demo/Expert-Searching-App/frontend/src/api/users.js)

Add three new functions:
- `fetchUsersSummary({ page, limit, search, filters })`
- `fetchUserFilterOptions()`
- `fetchUserFormLookups()`

---

## 4 — Impact Summary

| Page | Before | After | Improvement |
|------|--------|-------|-------------|
| **UsersPage** | 3 + 2N calls (≈43) | **2 calls** (summary + filter-options) | **~95% reduction** |
| **UserEditPage** | 3 calls | **2 calls** | **33% reduction** |
| **UserDetails** | 3 calls | 3 calls | No change — already efficient |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All changes are **additive** — new endpoints are added alongside existing ones. The existing `GET /users` endpoint remains untouched.

